<subSubSection id="BC0838C95D1EF386D29BBD4CBD3FFD51" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" type="caryocolum interalbicella species-group">
<paragraph id="6F9484A0031D164A3412F01A49ACBC64" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">
<taxonomicName id="B26690D4D6626D8806F3449B1E05CC95" authorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Caryocolum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Caryocolum interalbicella" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="interalbicella">
<emphasis id="2CCCA011249DEFBF85AD351578319B7D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">Caryocolum interalbicella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="934A93DF3FEDC01B31D586F022C6594C" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">
The 
<taxonomicName id="AF6FF978C5CFCE10D96CB841605A62CD" authorityName="Herrich-Schaffer" authorityYear="1854" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Caryocolum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Caryocolum interalbicella" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="interalbicella">
<emphasis id="CDBDF8C885FA3E21D3406628B7F50FEC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">Caryocolum interalbicella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species-group was defined by 
<bibRefCitation id="433415FBE21DB6C2EA7877AD9E548640" author="Huemer, P" journalOrPublisher="Historical Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" pagination="439 - 571" refId="B17" refString="Huemer, P, 1988. A taxonomic revision of Caryocolum (Lepidoptera: Gelechiidae). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History). Historical Series 57: 439 - 571" title="A taxonomic revision of Caryocolum (Lepidoptera: Gelechiidae). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History)." volume="57" year="1988">Huemer (1988)</bibRefCitation>
and is characterized in the male genitalia by the following characters: uncus long and narrow; tegumen very broad anteriorly, strongly constricted medially, with large pedunculi; transtilla with spines; valva usually long and slender, subbasally strongly bent, apex frequently bulged, with brush of setae; sacculus knife-shaped; posterior margin of vinculum medially incised to broadly emarginated; saccus slender to moderately broad; phallus without cornuti. Female genitalia are characterized by the following characters: segment VIII with pair of ventral or dorsal processes, ventromedial area sclerotized with or without microtrichia; antrum short ring to long funnel; signum with a semi-oval basal plate and a strong distal hook. The species-group includes 18 species (
<bibRefCitation id="D3F84F48F355579721EBA200055D0819" author="Huemer, P" journalOrPublisher="Historical Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" pagination="439 - 571" refId="B17" refString="Huemer, P, 1988. A taxonomic revision of Caryocolum (Lepidoptera: Gelechiidae). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History). Historical Series 57: 439 - 571" title="A taxonomic revision of Caryocolum (Lepidoptera: Gelechiidae). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History)." volume="57" year="1988">Huemer 1988</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="21ED6F2D2DDA7A1E927E8AE18B61417D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1163/9789004260986" author="Huemer, P" journalOrPublisher="Apollo Books, Stenstrup" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" refId="B20" refString="Huemer, P, Karsholt, O, 2010. Gelechiidae II (Gelechiinae: Gnorimoschemini). In: Huemer P, Karsholt O, Nuss M (Eds) Microlepidoptera of Europe. Vol. 6. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1163/9789004260986" title="Gelechiidae II (Gelechiinae: Gnorimoschemini). In: Huemer P, Karsholt O, Nuss M (Eds) Microlepidoptera of Europe. Vol. 6." url="https://doi.org/10.1163/9789004260986" year="2010">Huemer and Karsholt 2010</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="FDD12631FCAD63B8A668CA49022253A7" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.921.49197" author="Huemer, P" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" pagination="65 - 140" refId="B21" refString="Huemer, P, Karsholt, O, 2020. Commented checklist of European Gelechiidae (Lepidoptera). ZooKeys 921: 65 - 140, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.921.49197" title="Commented checklist of European Gelechiidae (Lepidoptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.921.49197" volume="921" year="2020">2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C85593622D7B3AAF5B31D8FEBE512D4" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">
The informal 
<taxonomicName id="F70E724B8A47CFFB9CF34BF56885A2E0" baseAuthorityName="Haworth" baseAuthorityYear="1812" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Caryocolum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Caryocolum tricolorella" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="189" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolorella">
<emphasis id="B77E954041AF876154C2FBE306DA1D23" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="189">Caryocolum tricolorella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subsection is characterized by a long and evenly slender valva without apical bulge in the male genitalia, and a large, broadly funnel-shaped antrum in the female genitalia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
